            {text: "Irrigation provides water for crops. If excessive irrigation without drainage occurs, which soil problem develops?", options: ["Improved fertility", "Waterlogging and salinization degrading soil", "Enhanced productivity", "No problems"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Organic farming avoids synthetic inputs. Which soil health improvement does organic matter addition provide?", options: ["Soil degradation", "Enhanced soil structure, biology, and fertility", "Nutrient depletion", "Soil compaction"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Drip irrigation delivers water directly to roots. Which water conservation advantage does drip irrigation provide over flooding?", options: ["Higher water waste", "Reduced water use through targeted application", "No water savings", "Increased runoff"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Rainwater harvesting captures precipitation. Which water security benefit does harvesting provide in dry regions?", options: ["No water benefit", "Supplemental water supply during dry periods", "Increased water shortage", "Flood creation"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Traffic accidents kill wildlife on roads. If 29% of wildlife mortality in Geralle National Park is from vehicles, which conservation strategy addresses this?", options: ["Build more roads", "Wildlife corridors and underpasses allowing safe crossing", "Increase traffic speed", "No mitigation needed"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Road ecology studies wildlife-road interactions. Which road design feature reduces animal collisions?", options: ["Higher traffic volume", "Wildlife fencing directing animals to crossing structures", "Faster speed limits", "No design changes"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Habitat connectivity allows animal movement. If roads fragment habitat, which population consequence results?", options: ["Enhanced gene flow", "Isolated populations with reduced genetic diversity", "Improved connectivity", "No population effect"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Population doubling time is time for population to double. If growth rate is 2% per year, which approximate doubling time results (Rule of 70)?", options: ["70 years", "35 years (70/2)", "140 years", "20 years"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Demographic transition describes development stages. In Stage 1, both birth and death rates are high. Which population growth characterizes Stage 1?", options: ["Rapid growth", "Slow growth due to high mortality offsetting high births", "Negative growth", "No growth"], correct: 1},
            {text: "In demographic transition Stage 2, death rates fall but birth rates remain high. Which rapid growth phase is this?", options: ["No growth", "Rapid population expansion as mortality falls", "Population decline", "Stable population"], correct: 1},
            {text: "In demographic transition Stage 3, birth rates decline. Which growth change occurs?", options: ["Accelerating growth", "Slowing growth as birth rates fall toward death rates", "No change", "Instant stabilization"], correct: 1},
            {text: "In demographic transition Stage 4, both rates are low. Which developed country pattern is this?", options: ["High growth", "Low or zero growth with aging population", "Rapid growth", "Exponential increase"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Replacement fertility is births maintaining population size. Why is replacement TFR approximately 2.1 rather than 2.0?", options: ["Ensures growth", "Accounts for mortality before reproductive age", "Random number", "Immigration adjustment"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Age dependency ratio compares dependents to working-age. If 40% are under 15 and 5% over 65, while 55% are working-age (15-64), what is the dependency ratio?", options: ["45:55 or about 0.82 dependents per working-age person", "55:45", "1:1", "2:1"], correct: 0},
            {text: "A youth bulge has large youth population. Which potential social outcome can youth bulges create?", options: ["Stable society", "Economic opportunity if jobs available, or instability if unemployment high", "Automatic development", "No social impact"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Urbanization concentrates population in cities. If rural areas depopulate, which agricultural labor consequence results?", options: ["Abundant farm labor", "Rural labor shortage requiring mechanization", "No labor change", "Increased farmers"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Migration affects both origin and destination. If skilled workers emigrate (brain drain), which origin country impact occurs?", options: ["Economic benefit", "Loss of human capital hindering development", "No impact", "Enhanced development"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Refugees flee persecution or conflict. If climate change displaces populations, which new migration category emerges?", options: ["No migration", "Environmental/climate refugees challenging traditional classifications", "Economic migrants only", "Normal migration"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Carrying capacity varies with technology. If agricultural technology increases food production, which carrying capacity change occurs?", options: ["Decreases", "Potentially increases allowing larger population", "No change possible", "Becomes zero"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Human ecological footprint measures resource demand. If consumption exceeds regeneration capacity, which condition exists?", options: ["Sustainable use", "Ecological overshoot depleting resources", "Balanced use", "Underconsumption"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Biodiversity provides ecosystem services. If species extinction reduces pollination, which agricultural consequence results?", options: ["Enhanced crop production", "Reduced crop yields from pollination loss", "No agricultural impact", "Improved farming"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Ecosystem resilience is recovery ability. If repeated disturbances prevent recovery, which state transition occurs?", options: ["Enhanced resilience", "Regime shift to alternative stable state", "Immediate recovery", "No state change"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Trophic cascades occur when top predators affect lower levels. If wolves are removed from an ecosystem, which cascade effect may result?", options: ["No ecosystem change", "Herbivore increase causing vegetation overgrazing", "Improved ecosystem balance", "Predator increase"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Eutrophication results from excess nutrients. If nitrogen and phosphorus runoff enters a lake, which oxygen consequence occurs?", options: ["Increased oxygen", "Hypoxia from algal bloom decomposition consuming oxygen", "No oxygen change", "Permanent high oxygen"], correct: 1},
            {text: "Indicator species reflect ecosystem health. If lichen disappears from an area, which environmental problem is indicated?", options: ["Improved air quality", "Air pollution as lichens are sensitive to pollutants", "No environmental issue", "Enhanced ecosystem health"], correct: 1}
